Purchase options and add-ons

  • New look, new sound – Echo delivers clear highs, dynamic mids, and deep bass for rich, detailed sound that automatically adapts to any room.
  • Voice control your entertainment – Stream songs from Amazon Music, Apple Music, SiriusXM, Spotify, Deezer, and more. Plus listen to radio stations, podcasts, and Audible audiobooks.
  • Ready to help – Ask Alexa to play music, answer questions, play the news, check the weather, set alarms, control compatible smart home devices, and more.

  • Designed to protect your privacy – Built with multiple layers of privacy protections and controls, including a microphone off button that electronically disconnects the microphones.

Meet the all-new Echo

Talk about well-rounded. Echo combines premium sound, a built-in Zigbee smart home hub, and a temperature sensor. Powerful speakers deliver clear highs, dynamic mids, and deep bass for rich, detailed sound that adapts to any room.

Just ask Alexa to play music, answer questions, make calls, and tell you the news, sports scores, weather, and more.

“Alexa, play music everywhere”

Use your voice to play a song, artist, or genre through Amazon Music, Apple Music, SiriusXM, Spotify, Deezer and others. With multi-room music, you can fill your whole home with music, radio stations, podcasts, and Audible using compatible Echo devices in different rooms. You can even pair with Fire TV to feel scenes come to life with home theater audio.

Voice control your home

The built-in smart home hub lets you easily set up and manage dozens of smart devices that use Zigbee. Just power on compatible lights, plugs, sensors, and locks and say, “Alexa, discover my devices.”

Alexa is happy to help

Make your life easier at home. Set timers, ask questions, add items to lists, and create calendar events and reminders. Check the traffic and weather, or play the news. Access many Alexa skills. You can even bring new life to game night with Question of the Day, Escape the Room, True or False and more.

Stay connected and in sync

Instantly drop in on other rooms in your home or make an announcement to every room that has a compatible Echo device. Let everyone know dinner is ready, or remind the kids that it’s bedtime. You can also stay in touch with friends and family with hands-free calling.

Designed to protect your privacy

Alexa and Echo devices are built with multiple layers of privacy protection. Echo smart speakers have a microphone off button that electronically disconnects the microphones. You also have control over your voice recordings and can view, hear, or delete them at any time. Learn more about Alexa privacy.

Simple to set up and use

1

Plug in Echo and connect to the internet with the Alexa app.

2

Just ask Alexa for music, weather, news, and more.

3

For simple setup with compatible smart home devices, say, “Alexa, discover my devices.”

Every day is an earth day

You don’t have to be an environmental scientist to make sustainable choices. We considered sustainability in the design of this device. Here’s how:

Device Materials

50% post-consumer recycled plastics
100% post-consumer recycled fabric
100% recycled die-cast aluminum
Device, cable and adapter included

Low Power Mode

To reduce its energy consumption, this device will enter Low Power Mode when it is idle. Low Power Mode is not available for certain user configurations. To learn more, see Low Power Mode Restrictions.

Device Packaging

99% of this device’s packaging is made of wood fiber-based materials from responsibly managed forests or recycled sources.

Technical details

Echo (4th Gen)

Size

144 mm x 144 mm x 133 mm

Weight

970 g. Actual size and weight may vary by manufacturing process.

Wifi connectivity

Dual-band wifi supports 802.11a/b/g/n/ac (2.4 and 5 GHz) networks. Does not support connecting to ad-hoc (or peer-to-peer) wifi networks.

Smart home connectivity

Smart home hub: Zigbee + Sidewalk + Matter + Thread border router

Bluetooth connectivity

Advanced Audio Distribution Profile (A2DP) support for audio streaming from your mobile device to Echo or from Echo to your Bluetooth speaker. Audio/Video Remote Control Profile (AVRCP) for voice control of connected mobile devices. Hands-free voice control is not supported for Mac OS X devices. Direct control of BLE Mesh. Bluetooth speakers requiring PIN codes are not supported.

eero Built-in

Your wifi network must use a compatible eero router and your Echo device must stay in range of a compatible eero device. You will need to link your eero and Amazon accounts and manage eero Built-in from the eero mobile application to use this feature. eero Built-in compatible Echo devices support up to 1,000 sq. ft. of additional coverage, speeds up to 100 Mbps, and 10 or fewer connected devices. Actual performance can vary and certain eero, Echo, or Alexa features may be incompatible with eero Built-in. Learn more about eero Built-in performance, availability and compatibility. Use of eero and eero-related products and services, including eero Built-in, requires creation of an eero account and agreement to eero’s Terms of Service. Review eero’s Privacy Notice.

Audio

76.2 mm neodymium woofer and two 20 mm tweeters.

Alexa app

The Alexa app is compatible with Fire OS, Android, and iOS devices. Supported operating systems.

Accessibility features

To enable features that personalize Alexa to your abilities, go to Settings → Accessibility in the Alexa App.
• Preferred Speaking Rate allows customers to control how fast or slow Alexa speaks. To enable, say “Alexa, speak slower” or “Alexa, speak faster.“
• Request Sound will play an audible tone in addition to the visual indicator when you speak to Alexa. To enable, say “Alexa, turn on Start of Request Sound.”
• Kindle Read Aloud will have Alexa read your Kindle books aloud.
• Alexa Accessibility features also include several other settings for customers with accessibility needs related to vision, hearing, mobility, and speech.

Warranty and service

1-year limited warranty and service included. Optional 1-year, 2-year, and 3-year extended warranty available for Canada customers sold separately. Use of Echo is subject to these terms.

Setup technology

Amazon wifi simple setup enables customers to connect smart devices to their wifi network in a few easy steps. Wifi simple setup is another way Alexa is always getting smarter. Learn more about wifi simple setup.

Included in the box

Echo (4th Gen), power adapter (30W), and Quick Start Guide.

Generation

Echo (4th Gen) - 2020 release

Privacy features

Wake word technology, streaming indicators, microphone off button, the ability to view and delete your voice recordings, and more. Visit the Alexa Privacy Hub to explore how Alexa and Echo devices are designed to protect your privacy.

Language

Alexa speaks both English and French. Say: “Alexa, speak French and English”. Learn more here. Not all skills are supported in both English and French. Please refer to the skills store here for more information.

Software Security Updates

This device receives guaranteed software security updates until at least four years after the device is last available for purchase as a new unit on our websites. Learn more about these software security updates. If you already own an Amazon Echo, visit Manage Your Content and Devices for information specific to your device.

5.0 out of 5 stars An Echo Upgrade for My Home Office
Reviewed in Canada on August 23, 2023
Colour Name: CharcoalConfiguration: EchoVerified Purchase
Rating: ★★★★★ (5/5)

I recently added the Echo (4th Gen) to my home office, and I must say, it's been a fantastic addition. This isn't my first Echo device, and I'm confident it won't be my last. Here's why I love it:

**Sound Quality (★★★★★):**
The sound quality of the Echo (4th Gen) is truly impressive. Whether I'm listening to music, having a conference call, or simply asking Alexa for information, the sound is clear, crisp, and fills the room beautifully. It makes working from home a much more enjoyable experience.

**Voice Recognition (★★★★★):**
One of the standout features of this Echo is its exceptional voice recognition. Alexa understands my commands and questions perfectly, even in a room with some background noise. It makes managing tasks and controlling smart devices in my office a breeze.

**Tech Support (★★★★★):**
As an experienced Echo user, I've rarely needed tech support. However, it's reassuring to know that Amazon provides excellent customer support for its devices. Should any issues arise, I'm confident they will be resolved promptly.

**Smart Home Hub (★★★★★):**
The Echo (4th Gen) doubles as a smart home hub, which is incredibly convenient. I can easily control my smart lights, thermostat, and even my coffee maker with just my voice. It's a game-changer for productivity and comfort in my home office.

**Overall Impressions (★★★★★):**
This Echo (4th Gen) has exceeded my expectations and has become an integral part of my home office setup. It combines premium sound quality, efficient voice recognition, and the convenience of a smart home hub in one sleek device. If you're considering upgrading your office or home setup, I highly recommend giving this Echo a try.

As someone who's had multiple Echo devices over the years, I can confidently say that Amazon continues to innovate and improve their products. I'm looking forward to what they come up with next, and I'm certain that Echo devices will remain a staple in my home.

In conclusion, the Echo (4th Gen) is a stellar addition to my home office, and I wouldn't hesitate to buy more for other rooms in my house. It's a versatile and high-quality smart speaker that offers a lot of value for the price. If you're a fan of Echo devices like I am, you won't be disappointed with this one.

Jean-P T.
4.0 out of 5 stars A few things could be improved
Reviewed in Canada on December 3, 2022
Verified Purchase
I like Alexa devices in general ... I have at least 7 in my home ...
This being said ..

# Stereo pairing
I tried pairing this one with my older echo to have stereo when listening to spotify but it was a bit complicated even for an IT guy.
The problem was that 1 echo device was on the 2ghz band and 1 was on the 5ghz band.
So Alexa complained that there were not on the same network but it's the same SSID and I think it should work fine anyway since they share the same network somehow.
The workaround I found was to go in my router settings, use mac filtering to block my new echo device from 5ghz band.

# When using my Samsung phone, Spotify steaming to Alexa does not always work, I press Play and there is no sound. It always works in the end but it's a bit annoying to have to re-try multiple times

# There are a few things Alexa has issues understanding, like some songs she can't find on Spotify for no apparent reason, it would be nice to have an easy way to report these so they can get fixed. I tried playing some playlists on Spotify but Alexa would not recognize them. Also for some reasons sometimes we say "close light XYZ" (in french) and it won't work, sometimes it does. Sometimes we say "turn of light XYZ" instead and this works. It's not consistent.

# When there is a power outage, often some lights can't be found by Alexa but they work in Kasa/Govee/etc. The workaround is to re-plug the plugs and to reset the switches but it's a bit annoying.

# In the Alexa app, often when we add a device in a group, it removes another device from that group

# There were notification sounds that we did not know why we got them and it was a bit annoying. Eventually I realized that it was when there was a "deal" on Amazon. I disabled it using the Alexa App and it seems fine now but I think this should be improved. Indeed, when I asked Alexa what why Alexa made a sound. she was not able to provide an answer. When looking at the history in the Alexa app, there was nothing about that "event". I think it's when I finally asked "do I have notifications?" that I was able to understand what was that sound. I think this should be replaced by Amazon Store alerts instead or on the phone notifications instead. Something you can look at instead of listening to. Visual instead of audio.

# Sound is OK as long as you don't crank it up too much, I might buy the Echo Studio eventually

Update 2023 : the alexa app on android is really due for a refresh, i have maybe 20 alexa supported devices in my house and the app feels quite outdated and slow, managing groups and rooms among other things can be quite painful .. troubleshooting network issues should also be improved
